						<summary>

						<p>Uttarāpatīśvara temple, Gaṇapatīśvara shrine, north wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājarāja (I) Year 29.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the gift of 3 <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> of land for the festival for Chiṟuttoṇḍa-nambi, who served the God Mahādēvar-Chīrāḷa-dēvar of Tiruchcheṅgāṭṭāṅkuḍi, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadānam</hi> in Marugā-nāḍu by Marugal-uḍaiyāṉ Tāḻiguṇanilai and Marukaluḍaiyāṉ Pūvan Nakkan, who had the <hi rend="italic">kāṇi</hi> of Iṟaiyāṉkuḍi which was the land of Marugā-kkō of Marukā-nāḍu in Mummuḍi-chōḻa-vaḷanāḍu. The donors undertook to pay the <hi rend="italic">iṟai</hi> on the land. The land appears to have been gifted in the name of Tiru-vīrabhadra. It is stated that these two individuals got the <hi rend="italic">kāṇi</hi> as above in the 17th and 18th years of the king after the survey <hi rend="italic">(ulagaḷandērina).</hi></p>						

						</summary>
